": \"org.slf4j:slf4j-api:1.7.31\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"JGroups declares SLF4J as an optional dependency and LogFactory/Slf4jLogImpl use it for the normal optional logging integration path.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.wildfly.openssl:wildfly-openssl:2.1.1.Final\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"JGroups SslContextFactory reflectively probes org.wildfly.openssl classes to enable its optional OpenSSL provider path, which is relevant reachability coverage for SSL configuration.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Set JGroups tests to loopback/IPv4 defaults before touching JGroups classes: `jgroups.bind_addr=127.0.0.1` and `java.net.preferIPv4Stack=true`; pass the same properties to native test runtime args. Prefer in-process stacks such as `SHARED_LOOPBACK` or loopback TCP over multicast/external cluster discovery. If testing logging defaults, be aware `LogFactory` reads `jgroups.use.jdk_logger` and `jgroups.log_class` during static initialization, so set or clear them before first use.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Real UDP multicast or default interface discovery can be flaky or unavailable in CI/native-image test environments.\",\n    \"Logging and SSL provider choices are static-initialization sensitive, so late property changes may not affect already initialized JGroups classes.\",\n    \"OpenSSL coverage may vary by platform/provider availability; local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0fb6003459d9fa98016a426dffc9d48196bf3cc0f5d55f6189\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2694, "output": 943, "cacheRead": 32256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35893, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782738420962, "